00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,740
So you probably need to take a deeper look

475
00:20:32,740 --> 00:20:35,460
at what may be happening during that stage.

476
00:20:35,460 --> 00:20:37,220
And because I work at a great place,

477
00:20:37,220 --> 00:20:38,500
everyone accepts their offer,

478
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:40,140
but wow, we lost the chance to hire women

479
00:20:40,140 --> 00:20:42,060
at the resume and onsite stages.

480
00:20:43,460 --> 00:20:48,460
This is hard, but it's really worth it.

481
00:20:49,180 --> 00:20:51,500
Since this problem is one of people and systems,

482
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,940
it's inherently challenging,

483
00:20:53,940 --> 00:20:54,860
especially if you're a person

484
00:20:54,860 --> 00:20:57,020
who's at the apex of privilege in our society.

485
00:20:57,020 --> 00:20:59,140
But do what you can.

486
00:20:59,140 --> 00:21:01,580
It's worth it to even go 50% of the way

487
00:21:01,580 --> 00:21:04,220
rather than not do anything.

488
00:21:05,380 --> 00:21:07,500
From one perfectionist to another,

489
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:09,340
admit that you won't have it perfect.

490
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:12,420
Try to build process around data collection

491
00:21:12,420 --> 00:21:13,860
wherever you can,

492
00:21:13,860 --> 00:21:15,860
and please don't guess about people

493
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:17,900
unless it's required by law

494
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:20,500
or outsourced to a company like a Typica

495
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:21,900
that does it professionally.

496
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:24,500
They're less likely to mess up than a biased human,

497
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,100
even a well-intentioned one.

498
00:21:27,060 --> 00:21:29,780
And if you are at the apex of privilege,

499
00:21:29,780 --> 00:21:32,380
ahem, cis whitehead men,

500
00:21:32,380 --> 00:21:34,580
you should involve people from underrepresented groups

501
00:21:34,580 --> 00:21:36,580
to be involved in the process.

502
00:21:36,580 --> 00:21:37,420
Listen to them,

503
00:21:37,420 --> 00:21:39,260
because they know how things are gonna come across,

504
00:21:39,260 --> 00:21:42,180
but please don't make them do the lion's share of the work.

505
00:21:42,820 --> 00:21:45,260
My recommendation is to solicit their opinion early and often,

506
00:21:45,260 --> 00:21:46,460
do some work,

507
00:21:46,460 --> 00:21:48,260
show them what you did and ask for feedback,

508
00:21:48,260 --> 00:21:50,820
but don't make them carry this whole boulder by themselves.

509
00:21:53,260 --> 00:21:55,020
So these are just some examples

510
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:57,380
of what I have done at Clover Health.

